      <section eId="sec_CCP-1911">
        <num>CCP 1911</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1911__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as otherwise provided by law, every final judgment shall contain the
typewritten or printed name of the judge and be signed by the judge.  Any judgment that does
not contain the typewritten or printed name of the judge shall not be invalidated for that
reason.  Judgments may be signed by the judge by use of electronic signature.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1911__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>For the purpose of an appeal as provided in Article 2083, no appeal shall be taken
from a final judgment until the judgment has been signed by the judge.
Amended by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111337</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
